10 and manner prescribed by the commissioner and pay a fee of twenty-five dollars.
11 The commissioner shall give a licensee at least sixtyninety days' notice of the
12 biennial license continuation filing deadline. A resident public adjuster or a
13 nonresident public adjuster who allows the license to lapse may, within the
14 twelve-month period immediately following the expiration date, reinstate the
15 same license without the necessity of passing a written examination, upon
16 payment of a reinstatement fee, not to exceed one hundred twenty-five dollars,
17 prescribed by the commissioner in addition to the renewal fee.
18 c. The commissioner may grant an individual licensee who is unable to comply with
19 license renewal procedures due to military service or some other extenuating
20 circumstance, including a long-term medical disability, a waiver of an examination
21 requirement or a fine, fee, or sanction imposed for failure to comply with renewal
22 procedures.
23 2. The commissioner shall issue a business entity public adjuster license to a business
24 entity that meets the necessary requirements of this chapter.
25 a. A business entity public adjuster license expires on the last day of the month
