2 SECTION 6. AMENDMENT. Section 26.1-26.8-11 of the North Dakota Century Code is
3 amended and reenacted as follows:
4 26.1-26.8-11. Proof of bond or insurance.
5 1. At the time of issuance of a resident public adjuster license or a nonresident public
6 adjuster license and for the duration of the license, an applicant shall maintain a surety
7 bond or proof of insurance satisfactory to the commissioner for the use and benefit of
8 the commissioner for insureds that have remitted fees, retainers, compensation,
9 deposits, or other things of value to the public adjuster in the course of the public
10 adjuster's business. The bond:
11 a. Must be a minimum of twenty thousand dollars; and
12 b. May not be terminated by the surety company or public adjuster unless written
13 notice has been filed with the commissioner and submitted to the public adjuster
14 at least sixtythirty days before the termination.
15 2. The commissioner may request the evidence of financial responsibility at any time the
16 commissioner deems relevant.
17 3. A public adjuster immediately shall notify the commissioner if evidence of financial
18 responsibility terminates or becomes impaired. The authority to act as a public
19 adjuster automatically terminates if the evidence of financial responsibility terminates
20 or becomes impaired.
21 SECTION 7. AMENDMENT. Section 26.1-26.8-12 of the North Dakota Century Code is
22 amended and reenacted as follows:
23 26.1-26.8-12. Continuing education.
24 1. Except as otherwise provided in this section, an individual who holds a resident public
25 adjuster license or a nonresident public adjuster license shall satisfactorily complete a
26 minimum of twenty-four credits of continuing education, including three credits of
27 ethics, reported on a biennial basis in conjunction with the license renewal cycle.
28 Credits for continuing education courses attended in any one year over the minimum
29 number of hours of education required, not to exceed twelve hours, may be credited to
30 the year next preceding the year in which the credits were earned or to the year next
31 following the year in which the credits were earned. Report of continuing education
